<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST /LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: MAN GETS 5 YEARS IN KILLING AT RESTAURANT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 23-year-old Sylmar man was sentenced Thursday to five years in prison for 
killing a 21-year-old Los Angeles man during an argument outside a Reseda 
restaurant last year. 
</P>
<P>
Van Nuys Superior Court Judge Alan B. Haber sentenced Inho Kim for voluntary 
manslaughter in the April 27, 1989, shooting death of Hong Soon Lim. 
</P>
<P>
Kim shot Lim once in the head with a .357 magnum revolver in the parking lot of 
Seoul Seoul Restaurant on Louise Avenue after an argument in the restaurant's 
bar. 
</P>
<P>
Kim was originally charged with murder but was convicted of the lesser charge 
on April 5 after a non-jury trial. 
</P>
</TEXT>
