<HEADLINE>
<P>
REYNOLDS RESIGNS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I am appalled to learn that Ann Reynolds has resigned (as chancellor of the 
20-campus California State University) over the controversy surrounding her 
appreciable pay raise (Part A, April 21). She perhaps was awarded this raise in 
a procedure that can be criticized, but the point is that her position has been 
seriously underpaid for a decade and deserves a compensation level comparable 
to her University of California counterpart. 
</P>
<P>
The salary of David Gardner is in excess of $230,600. The trustees of CSU 
rightfully should raise her salary from $136,248 to $195,000. She supervises a 
budget of $2 billion, encompassing 20 exceptional universities. Reynolds' 
salary is appropriate to her responsibilities and her headaches. 
</P>
<P>
RICHARD MOORE 
</P>
<P>
Superintendent and President 
</P>
<P>
Santa Monica College 
</P>
</TEXT>
