<HEADLINE>
<P>
ART CENSORSHIP IN CINCINNATI 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In response to your editorial "Censorship in Cincinnati" (April 10), please 
spare me your superior attitude. Since when is pedophilia or sadomasochism 
something to be celebrated? Or tolerated? There seems to be a general campaign 
by civil libertarians to silence those who oppose this point of view by 
referring to them as unsophisticated yahoos. 
</P>
<P>
It is an effort to desensitize people which I pray to God fails. I am not sure 
how this type of display can be prevented without endangering the very real 
cultural benefits of the National Endowment for the Arts. We might start by 
reminding those in charge that "what we tolerate, we learn to accept, and 
eventually embrace." It is a thought I can hardly bear. 
</P>
<P>
MRS. HAZEL R. ELLIOTT 
</P>
<P>
Long Beach 
</P>
</TEXT>
