<HEADLINE>
<P>
ANIMAL SYMPATHIZERS 'BITE BACK' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
What right has E. Edward Kavanaugh, president of the Cosmetic, Toiletry &amp; 
Fragrance Assn., to speak of animal rights compared to a child's life? 
</P>
<P>
His association's members use animals in experiments for perfumes, cosmetics 
and soap -- horrific experiments where the animals suffer dreadfully; 
experiments that have nothing to do with saving a child's life. 
</P>
<P>
Let the CTFA use the million dollars put aside to fight animal rights on 
finding more appropriate humane research techniques. 
</P>
<P>
PAMELA W. ELLIS 
</P>
<P>
Woodland Hills 
</P>
</TEXT>
