<HEADLINE>
<P>
CHARGERS TO OPEN SEASON AT DALLAS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Chargers will open the newly formatted 17-week NFL schedule Sept. 9 at 
Dallas and be idle Dec. 9 before finishing with three games against AFC West 
opponents, the team announced Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
The Chargers, who have opened on the road 15 of the past 18 seasons and have a 
record of 8-7 in those games, return for their home opener Sept. 16 against the 
Cincinnati Bengals, who haven't played in San Diego since 1982. 
</P>
<P>
ESPN will nationally televise the Chargers' Nov. 25 game against the Seattle 
Seahawks beginning at 5 p.m. 
</P>
