<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRITISH SEIZE A RECORD 660 POUNDS OF COCAINE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
LONDON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
British customs officials Wednesday seized a record cocaine haul of 660 pounds 
worth about $66 million from a ship docked in Liverpool, the Press Assn. news 
service reported. 
</P>
<P>
Investigators searching the Sun Tempest uncovered 240 pounds of the drug 
Wednesday, it reported. They had recovered 418 pounds from the same ship 
Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
"We have now seized 660 pounds of cocaine from the ship. This makes it the 
biggest cocaine seizure in Britain," a customs spokesman said. 
</P>
<P>
The Sun Tempest arrived in Britain on Tuesday from Peru and Chile. 
