<P>
BOY STOPS CAR AFTER MOTHER PASSES OUT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 5-year-old boy steered a runaway car to safety on a freeway after his mother 
apparently passed out at the wheel, the California Highway Patrol said. "My 
mommy's dead! My mommy's dead!" the boy screamed after the car was brought to a 
halt by an off-duty Alameda County firefighter who drove his pickup truck in 
front of the car to slow it. 
</P>
<P>
Firefighter Brian Bailey said he checked the woman's pulse and breathing and 
reassured the boy that his mother was alive. The boy said his mother had been 
drinking, Bailey said. He said the car was going about 25 m.p.h. down a slight 
grade when he brought it to a stop near a freeway exit. The impact crunched the 
back of his pickup. CHP Officer Casey Simpson said Kathy Graves, 31, of Castro 
Valley, was arrested on suspicion of drunk driving. Her son, Anthony, was 
placed in temporary foster care. 
