<P>
Carolco Sells TV Rights: Carolco Pictures, maker of the popular Rambo movies, 
said it has sold West German and French television rights to a package of 
feature films for more than $50 million. The West German agreement with Hermes 
Synchron calls for 34 films from Carolco's library to be broadcast in West 
Germany, East Germany, Austria and other German-speaking territories. The 
French deal, signed with Aries SA, also involves 34 films to be broadcast on 
French commercial and pay TV. 
