<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: FORMER POLICE CHIEF APPOINTED TO OLD POST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Former Police Chief Robert Collins, 66, has been appointed to his old post in 
Monterey Park, replacing Kenneth Hickman, who resigned in March amid a 
controversy over control of the Police Department. 
</P>
<P>
Collins, a 34-year veteran of the force, was chief from 1987 to 1989, replacing 
another chief, Jon D. Elder, who had left as part of a local political 
firestorm. 
</P>
<P>
"He's really well respected in the community and within the police force," City 
Manager Mark Lewis said of Collins. 
</P>
<P>
Hickman, a former Los Angeles police commander and one of the nation's few 
chiefs with a doctorate, had replaced Collins when Collins retired. Hickman 
resigned after the Monterey Park Police Officers Assn. voted no confidence in 
him. 
