<P>
TODAY AT AFI FESTIVAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Sheila Benson, Compiled by Michael Wilmington 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Following are the Times' recommendations for today's schedule of the American 
Film Institute Los Angeles International Film Festival, with commentary by the 
film-reviewing staff. Information: (213) 480-3232 or (213) 520-2000. 
</P>
<P>
Highly recommended: 
</P>
<P>
"Heart of the Warrior"(U.S./Finland; Director: Stephen Peck; Century Plaza, 7 
p.m.). A compassionate, wrenchingly well-made film. Two wounded veterans of 
Vietnam and Afghanistan revisit the countries where they fought and compare 
experiences as amputees. The Afghan vet suggests that "people's heartlessness" 
must not get the better of them. In the face of films like this, heartlessness 
is not even a possibility. 
</P>
<P>
Recommended: 
</P>
<P>
"Berkeley in the '60s"(U.S.; Director: Mark Kitchell; AFI Mark Goodson, 9 
p.m.). Outstanding, a careful, balanced job on a complex, many-layered subject. 
Sheila Benson 
</P>
