<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: COUNTYWIDE; 
</P>
<P>
FIRE OFFICIALS WARN OF SOLICITORS' SCAM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The County Fire Department is cautioning the public against phone solicitors 
misrepresenting themselves as firefighters asking for donations. 
</P>
<P>
"The Fire Department is receiving between 15 and 20 calls a day with complaints 
or queries about the solicitations," spokeswoman Kathleen Cha said. 
</P>
<P>
She said solicitors have been "abusive, rude and suspicious in nature." 
</P>
<P>
The Orange County Burn Assn. currently is the only legitimate charity using 
solicitors to advertise the department's benefit magic show scheduled May 30 in 
the Anaheim Convention Center, she said. 
</P>
<P>
The County Fire Department itself does not solicit by phone, Cha said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
