<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
IRVINE'S WOMEN GAIN TENNIS SEMIFINALS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The UC Irvine women's tennis team defeated Fresno State, 5-4, Thursday to 
advance to today's semifinals of the Big West Conference tournament at Ojai. 
</P>
<P>
Irvine (11-18) will face San Diego State, the four-time defending Big West 
champion, at 10 a.m. today at the Ojai Valley Racquet Club. 
</P>
<P>
UC Santa Barbara and Nevada Las Vegas, which beat Cal State Fullerton, 5-1, 
will meet in the other semifinal. 
</P>
<P>
The Anteaters and Bulldogs were tied, 3-3, but the doubles teams of Ali 
Yoshimoto and Michelle Foster, at No. 2, and Erin Abe and Jennifer Mazgedian, 
at No. 3, picked up victories. 
</P>
<P>
Fresno State defeated Irvine, 8-1, earlier this season. 
</P>
<P>
In California Collegiate Athletic Assn. baseball: 
</P>
<P>
Chapman 6, Cal State Los Angeles 3 -- Mark Landeros hit a three-run home run to 
lead visiting Chapman (25-19, 14-10). 
</P>
<P>
</P>
<P>
In nonconference baseball: 
</P>
<P>
Southern California College 5, UC San Diego 0 -- Doug Rystrom (4-3) pitched a 
four-hitter, struck out eight and walked seven to lead host Southern California 
College (26-15-1). Rystrom had two hits, three stolen bases and one RBI, and 
Rafael Garcia and Joe Aversa each hit solo home runs. 
</P>
