<HEADLINE>
<P>
KOCE AIRING 'SECRET ARMY' EXCLUSIVELY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By RICK VANDERKNYFF 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 42-part BBC dramatic series, "Secret Army," will begin airing Thursday on 
Channel 50, Huntington Beach-based KOCE-TV. 
</P>
<P>
Set in Belgium during World War II, the series, which will continue every 
Thursday at 9 p.m., focuses on the organization called Lifeline that helped 
Allied servicemen escape from the Nazis. "Secret Army" will not be shown by any 
other Southern California channels. 
</P>
<P>
Also on KOCE, the accomplishments of Southeast Asian refugees in Orange County 
will be explored by reporter Jim Cooper on "The Southeast Asians: An American 
Success Story," a public affairs special airing Sunday at 5 p.m. and Monday at 
9 p.m. RICK VANDERKNYFF 
</P>
</TEXT>
