<P>
THANK YOU FOR NOT BASHING CHRISTIANS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Bravo! Bravo! There's been so many nasty things said recently about religion, 
Christianity in particular. 
</P>
<P>
Some deserved, some not deserved. I was pleasantly shocked by Susan Christian's 
piece "The Last Temptation" (April 5). It was good, fair journalism. No 
Christian bashing. I almost fainted. 
</P>
<P>
I, for one, am glad the Church is offering these services to the gay community. 
After all, it's terribly convenient to donate a few bucks to the (AIDS) cause, 
sit back, put your feet up and blame God by assuming that homosexuals don't 
want any help . . . and couldn't change even if they did. Some folks call it a 
cop-out. 
</P>
<P>
Thanks again (Susan and The Times), and give us more. 
</P>
<P>
Wiley B. Burnes, 
</P>
<P>
Westminster 
</P>
