<P>
DISGRACED HONECKER ELUSIVE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
BEELITZ, East Germany 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Disgraced former East German leader Erich Honecker dodged photographers today 
when he was seen strolling through woods at the Soviet military hospital where 
he now lives under guard. 
</P>
<P>
Showing remarkable alertness for his 77 years, the once-feared former Communist 
Party chief and head of state spotted the cameras as he emerged from the forest 
with two uniformed Soviet army officers. 
</P>
<P>
As Honecker ducked behind a tree and poked his head around the trunk, one of 
the officers escorted the photographers away from the grounds of the hospital, 
a military sanatorium near Potsdam. 
</P>
</TEXT>
