<HEADLINE>
<P>
P. M. BRIEFING; 
</P>
<P>
AVON PULLS PLUG ON JAPAN DEAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NEW YORK 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Avon Products Inc., the cosmetics and jewelry giant, said today that it has 
terminated the sale of its profitable Avon Japan unit to two Japanese firms but 
plans to resume talks with other bidders. 
</P>
<P>
The company has operated in Japan for 20 years with a network of 350,000 sales 
representatives. It announced the sale of the unit in February for $450 
million. 
</P>
<P>
The company, facing a takeover threat from a dissident investor group, has been 
trying to reduce its $696 million in debt and boost its profits. The sale of 
the Japan unit would go a long way toward achieving that goal. 
</P>
</TEXT>
