<P>
NAMES IN THE NEWS; 
</P>
<P>
LELAND'S SONS LEAVE HOSPITAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
HOUSTON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The twin sons of the late Rep. Mickey Leland (D-Tex.) have finally gone home 
from the hospital. 
</P>
<P>
Cameron George and Austin Mickey Leland had been hospitalized in Houston for 
more than four months after being born 10 weeks prematurely. 
</P>
<P>
Leland's wife, Alison, said the babies, who weighed 3 pounds and 2 pounds, 11 
ounces at birth, now weigh about 8 pounds each. "They have turned into fat, 
healthy babies," she said. Alison Leland was about six weeks pregnant when her 
husband was killed in an Aug. 7 plane crash in Ethiopia while on a hunger 
relief mission. 
</P>
</TEXT>
