<P>
TESTS RUN ON GAME SHOW HOST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Game show host Bert Convy, 50, was in fair condition and underwent tests 
Thursday to determine why he collapsed during a hospital visit with his mother. 
</P>
<P>
"They are still running some tests to try to figure out why he passed out," 
said Ron Wise, spokesman at Cedars-Sinai Medical Center. "His condition is 
listed as fair and he's stable." On Sunday, the "Win, Lose or Draw" host was 
visiting his mother, Monica, who has been hospitalized for a stroke, and he 
passed out, Wise said. The nature of the tests wasn't disclosed. 
</P>
</TEXT>
