KANSAS CITY HOCKEY TEAM PICKS NAMED BLADES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
KANSAS CITY, Mo. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The owners of a new hockey team scheduled to begin play next season in Kansas 
City announced that the team will be called the Blades. 
</P>
<P>
Russ and Diane Parker, owners of the International Hockey League club, said 
they wanted a name with strong hockey connotations. 
</P>
<P>
"This clearly identifies us as a hockey club," Russ Parker said Thursday. 
</P>
