<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE SIDELINES; 
</P>
<P>
3 BASKETBALL PLAYERS ARRESTED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
MANSFIELD, La. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Three members of Northwestern State University's women's basketball team -- 
including the top scorer last season -- have been arrested and accused of 
burglaries in two parishes. 
</P>
<P>
The three Lady Demons told authorities they "were just out drinking . . . and 
lost their minds," said Pleasant Hill Marshal Clyde Callens, who arrested two 
of the players. 
</P>
<P>
Booked Thursday in DeSoto Parish on two counts of burglary were Iris Dixon, 20, 
a junior starting guard and the leading scorer; Tammy Blankenship, 19, a 
sophomore guard; and Tami Knotts, 18, a freshman point guard. 
</P>
<P>
They also were charged with burglary in Sabine Parish. 
</P>
</TEXT>
